\int\!\sqrt{\cot x}\,dx 
I_1=\int (\sqrt{\tan x}+\sqrt{\cot x})dx
 x=\arctan t^2\implies dx= \frac{2t}{1+t^4}dt
I_1=2\int \frac{t(t+\frac{1}{t})}{1+t^4}dt=2\int \frac{1+\frac{1}{t^2}}{(t-\frac{1}{t})^2+2}dt
t-\frac{1}{t}=z\implies (1+\frac{1}{t^2})dt=dz
I_1=2\int \frac{1}{z^2+2}dz =\sqrt{2}\tan^{-1}\left(\frac{z}{\sqrt{2}}\right)+c=\sqrt{2}\tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\sqrt{\tan x}-\sqrt{\cot x}}{\sqrt{2}}\right)+c
I_2=\int (\sqrt{\tan x}-\sqrt{\cot x})dx
(t+1/t)^2-1
t+1/t=z
I_2
I_3=\int \sqrt{\cot x}dx=\frac{I_1-I_2}{2}
